// Java Quizz related found in https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/java_online_quiz.htm// https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/java_online_quiz.htm Quizz Review
Q 1 - What of the following is the default value of an instance variable? Q 2 - Can we have two public classes in one java file? Q 3 - What is the default value of short variable? Q 4 - Which of the following statements are false about default modifier of class members? Q 5 - Which definitions below are not correct about local variable? Q 6 - Composition represents Q 7 - Method Overloading is an example of (select all the wrong answers) Q 8 - What is Serialization? Q 9 - Can a top level class be private or protected? Q 10 - Which of the following is a thread safe?
// Context question 1 null 0 Depends upon the type of variable Not assigned Answer : C Explanation: Instance variables are assigned default values based on their types. For example, int variable is assigned 0 and an object type variable is assigned null as default value.
// Context question 2 True False Answer : B Explanation: No, a java file can contain only one public class.
// Context question 3 0.0 0 null not defined Answer : B Explanation: short variable has default value of 0 if defined as an instance/static variable.
//Context question 4 By default, variables, methods and constructors can be accessed by subclass only. By default, variables, methods and constructors can be accessed by any class lying in any package By default, variables, methods and constructors can be accessed by any class lying in the same package. None of the above. Answer : A,B,D Explanation: By default, variables, methods and constructors can be accessed by any class lying in the same package.
// Context question 5 Variables defined inside methods, constructors or blocks are called local variables. Variables defined outside methods, constructors or blocks are called local variables. Static variables defined outside methods, constructors or blocks are called local variables. None of the above. Answer : B,C,D Explanation: Variables defined inside methods, constructors or blocks are called local variables. The variable will be declared and initialized within the method and it will be destroyed when the method has completed.
// Context question 6 HAS-A relationship IS-A relationship Answer : A Explanation: Holding the reference of the other class within some other class is known as composition. It represents a HAS-A relationship. For example, a Student has a Pen. Here Student class has Pen as its instance variable.
// Context question 7 Static Binding. Dynamic Binding. Both of the above. None of the above. Answer : B,C,D Explanation: Method Overloading is example of static binding.
// Context question 8 Serialization is the process of writing the state of an object to another object. Serialization is the process of writing the state of an object to a byte stream. Both of the above. None of the above. Answer : B Explanation: Serialization is the process of writing the state of an object to a byte stream.
// Context question 9 True False Answer : B Explanation: No, a top level class can not be private or protected. It can have either "public" or no modifier.
// Context question 10 StringBuilder StringBuffer Both of the above none of the above Answer : B StringBuffer is thread safe.
